==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: ketchup
<hw>ketch"up</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Probably of East Indian origin, because it was originally a kind
of East Indian pickles. Cf. also Malay <ets>k⟦ecr⟧chap</ets> fish sauce.
<au>MW10</au>.]</ety> <def>A pureed table sauce made predominantly from
tomatoes, flavored with onions, sugar, salt and spices; called also
<altname>tomato ketchup</altname>. The term is also applied to pureed
sauces containing mushrooms, walnuts, etc., being called in such cases
<altname>mushroom ketchup</altname>, <altname>walnut ketchup</altname>,
etc.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>catsup</asp> and
<asp>catchup</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ketine</ent>⟦br⟧
